{"title": "History of Greece to the Death of Alexander the Great, Vol I", "description": "J. B. Bury wrote his \u201cHistory of Greece\u201d before World War I, but it was such a good overview of classical Greek history that the third edition was still being used as a college textbook in the late 1960\u2032s. In the newer editions, a co-author rewrote the material dealing with the early centuries where there have been new archeological developments, but the later chapters and Bury\u2019s framework were retained essentially unchanged. Bury writes in a lucid, easily understood style that entertains as it educates. The book covers artistic and literary development, as well as politics and war, and its field of view includes western Asia Minor, the Agean archipelago, and \u201cGreater Greece\u201d (Sicily and Southern Italy). (Summary by Karen Merline) <br /><br />\n<a href=\"http://librivox.org/hist-of-greece-to-death-of-alexander-vol2-by-j-b-bury/\">LibriVox Recording of A History of Greece to the Death of Alexander the Great Vol II</a>", "duration": 75082, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "605", "name": "John Bagnell Bury"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt11/History_Greece_Death_Alexander_Great_Vol1_1111.jpg", "copyright_year": "1913", "genres": ["Antiquity"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Karen Merline"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Cori Samuel"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction and Prefaces", "readers": [1482], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greece_to_alexander1_0803_librivox1/historyofgreece1_00_bury_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1183}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1, part 1-2", "readers": [1343], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/greece_to_alexander1_0803_librivox1/historyofgreece1_01_bury_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1859}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 1, part 3", "readers": [1323], "path": "https://www